<FIRST>r i PM-BRF---Canada-Mine     02-21 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF---Canada-Mine,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gold Mine Cave-In Kills Three</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TIMMINS, Ontario (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cave-in in a gold mine shaft killed
three miners in this northeastern Ontario city, the mine manager
said.
   The three bodies were brought up from a depth of 1,200 feet about
five hours after Monday's accident, said Robert Perry, general
manager of the Placer Dome mine near the Quebec border.
   One member of a four-man mining crew, who was above ground when
the cave-in occurred, had reported his fellow miners missing, Perry
said.
   Union and mine officials said they would conduct separate
investigations into the cause of the cave-in.
   It was the second fatal accident in a year at the mine, which
began operating in 1910. A worker was killed in May when he fell
down an ore chute.
</TEXT>
