<FIRST>r a PM-Wash.Quake     02-21 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wash. Quake,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Minor Earthquake Shakes Washington State</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GOLDEN, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A minor earthquake shook Seattle suburbs,
but there were no reports of damage, said the National Earthquake
Information Center here.
   The quake occurred at 10:48 p.m. PST Monday about 20 miles
southwest of Seattle and registered 3.0 on the Richter scale, the
center said.
   The quake was felt in the south Seattle suburbs of Federal Way,
Renton, Enumclaw and Skyway, the center said.
   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on
seismographs. Every increase of one number means a tenfold increase
in magnitude. Thus a reading of 7.5 reflects an earthquake 10 times
stronger than one of 6.5.
   An earthquake of 3.5 on the scale can cause slight damage.
</TEXT>
