for consultations today, a day after the European Economic Community
countries recalled their envoys to protest Iran's death threats
against against novelist Salman Rushdie.
   Iran's ambassador to Sweden Daniesh Yazdi was informed of the
decision when he was summoned to Sweden's Ministry of Foreign
