<FIRST>r f PM-Earns-Zenith     02-21 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Earns-Zenith,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Electonics Company Announces Profitable Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GLENVIEW, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Zenith Electronics Corp. reported today
that its earnings soared in the fourth quarter and that it had an
annual profit for the first time in four years.
   Net income for the final quarter of 1988 totaled $20.4 million,
or 78 cents a share, compared with earnings of $4.7 million, or 18
cents a share, in 1987. Sales rose 23 percent, to $841 million from
$686 million.
   For the year, Zenith netted $11.7 million, or 45 cents per share,
vs. a $19.1 million loss. Sales were $2.7 billion, up 14 percent
from $2.4 billion in 1987.
   Company officials attributed the increase largely to sales of
computer products.
   ``There's finally a realization that Zenith can stay in consumer
electronics and make money,'' said Julian Menear, an analyst with
the the investment firm of Pershing &amp; Co.
</TEXT>
