<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-BankEarns     02-21 0164</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Bank Earns,0171</SECOND>
<HEAD>Natwest Profit More Than Doubles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   National Westminster Bank PLC, Britain's biggest
bank, reported Tuesday that its profit more than doubled in 1988.
   The company attributed the improvement to a sharply lower
loan-loss provision and narrower losses at its investment banking
unit.
   Natwest said its net income for the year came to $1.65 billion,
or $2.16 a share, compared with $755 million, or $1 a share, in 1987.
   Natwest added $86 million to its loan-loss provision in the
latest year, compared with $989 million in 1987.
   Natwest's investment banking unit, which is the holding company
for the County Natwest Investment Bank and its brokerage unit,
County Natwest Securities Ltd., posted a pre-tax loss of $99 million
in 1988, an improvement from a $204 million in 1987.
   Group Chief Executive Tom Frost said Natwest was ``poised for
further good progress and increased profitability.''
   The bank didn't break out quarterly or half-year results. It
isn't required to under British law.
</TEXT>
