<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Comsat     02-21 0225</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Comsat,0234</SECOND>
<HEAD>Comsat Earnings Rise In Fourth Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communications Satellite Corp. on Tuesday
reported a three-fold increase in fourth-quarter earnings, helping
the company to a 38 percent increase in earnings for all of 1988.
   Comsat provides communication services by satellite.
   ``Our results in 1988 proved that the decisive actions we took in
1987 to consolidate and redirect Comsat were the right ones,'' said
Irving Goldstein, chairman and chief executive officer. ``We expect
another strong performance in 1989 even though it may not be another
record year.''
   For the fourth quarter of 1988, net income was $12.4 million, or
66 cents per share, on revenues of $91.8 million. Earnings for the
fourth quarter of 1987 were $4.1 million, or 22 cents per share.
After adjusting for non-recurring items, net income from continuing
operations for the fourth quarter of 1987 would have been $6.5
million, or 36 cents per share.
   Revenue for the quarter rose to $91.8 million from $82.2 million.
   For all of 1988, Comsat earnings were a record $61.9 million, in
comparison with a loss a year earlier of $47.3 million. Excluding a
loss from discontinued operations, the company had a $17.8 million
profit in 1987.
   Revenue for the year was nearly $359 million _ up 8 percent from
$334 million in 1987. Earnings per share for the year were $3.35.
</TEXT>
